      {
        "id": 2328331,
        "name": "Philip Ente",
        "username": "Philip_Ente",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/philip_ente/{size}/964_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-01-03T03:37:34.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>          <iframe class=\"vimeo-onebox\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/245919615?h=6da0f14667&amp;app_id=122963\" data-original-href=\"https://vimeo.com/245919615\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\" seamless=\"seamless\" sandbox=\"allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-forms allow-popups allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox allow-presentation\"></iframe>\n</p>\n<p>1- Cousin Arnaud\u2019s prices are now out of reach for me, so time to look elsewhere.</p>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p>Benoit (note the resemblance) is really blossoming . He is cutting down on the acidity and the wines he gave me last month were far more complex and balanced than before.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Even though this is in French I think you can see that Benoit has a passion and INTELLIGENCE  ( I was present when he was having a conversation with Aubert de Villaine and half of what they were saying was beyond me) that I have only found in 2-3 local Santa Barbara Winemakers. These people spend far more time in the vineyard and less in the tasting room/promoting than the local people.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Yeah- I  know- more elitism/snobbism</p>\n</li>\n</ol>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 7,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-03T02:25:04.662Z",
