      {
        "id": 2328379,
        "name": "\u041c\u0430\u0458\u043a\u043b \u0420\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u0432",
        "username": "m_ristev",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/m_ristev/{size}/258749_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-01-03T05:41:37.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>i wonder what spurred on the demand, just a year ago i was still finding 1er cru from arnaud for around $100.  although this year i did manage la seve du clos for a reasonable rate.</p>\n<p>benoit has definitely improved a lot especially around the 2011 vintage.  i really regret not buying more of the 2014 en la richarde when zachys had a huge clearance.</p>\n<p>do you know the exact details of how arnaud ended up with benoit\u2019s parcel of puligny champ gains?</p>",
