        "username": "Philip_Ente",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/philip_ente/{size}/964_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-01-04T15:44:25.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"m. ristev\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n m. ristev:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>i wonder what spurred on the demand, just a year ago i was still finding 1er cru from arnaud for around $100.  although this year i did manage la seve du clos for a reasonable rate.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I think it started two years ago when Michel Bettaine  named Arnaud  winemaker of the year.<br>\nI was  very  surprised  last month when I ran into several extremely  wine competent people  in Cote de Beaune  who feel that Arnaud  is now one of the 2-3  top  producers there.</p>",
